{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 VBWD \u8212- Next 90 Days, Honest Plan\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Author context.} Solo developer. Full-time job elsewhere. Available bandwidth for VBWD: realistically {\b 8\u8211-12 hours/week}, occasionally 20 in a burst week. Wants to {\b minimise direct contact with merchants and end users}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Targets the plan must hit.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Brutto \u8364 ?100k within 12 months} (May 2026 \u8594 ? May 2027).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Brutto \u8364 ?300k within 24 months} (May 2026 \u8594 ? May 2028) \u8212- interpreted as cumulative two-year revenue.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b TL;DR.} The existing Owner Business Plan ($73k Y1, $192k Y2) assumes 48\u8211-50 hrs/week of founder time, ~37% custom dev (consulting), and active partner recruitment. {\b None of that survives the actual constraints.} Hitting \u8364 ?100k in 12 months on 10 hrs/week with no synchronous selling requires a very different revenue mix \u8212- license-led, marketplace-led, partner-led, all async. This document is the realistic version.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
