{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 4. The 90-day execution plan\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Working budget: {\b 8\u8211-12 hrs/week, 1 burst weekend per month.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The plan is sequenced so the {\b revenue-generating SKUs ship before the marketing}, because launching to no audience is wasted oxygen if there's nothing to buy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 1\u8211-2 \u8212- Productize what already exists (no new code)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Goal: turn the existing platform + decks into something a stranger can buy in 5 minutes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Pick {\b one} primary positioning for the launch. Recommend: {\b "Self-hosted Lemon Squeezy / Gumroad alternative"} (Bucket B). Why: clearest pain, biggest top-of-funnel, the math slide already exists, Gumroad refugee migration is a real ongoing wave.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Pricing page live on {\f1 vbwd.io} (or whatever the production domain is). 4 SKUs (Community / Starter / Pro / Lifetime-launch). Stripe Payment Link per SKU. {\b No "contact us" button.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? License-key delivery webhook tested end-to-end. Buy \u8594 ? email \u8594 ? key.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Repurpose {\f1 softwarestore} deck into the landing page hero. The decks are already written.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? One-page comparison table: VBWD vs Gumroad vs Lemon Squeezy vs Paddle vs Polar.sh. Honest. Include where they win.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Set up Plausible (or PostHog free tier) on the landing page. You need to see what converts.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Output:} something a stranger can land on, understand, and pay for, with zero email exchange.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 3\u8211-4 \u8212- Demo and docs (the "shop floor")\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Goal: docs do the selling so you don't have to.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Public demo instance permanently live at {\f1 demo.vbwd.io} (admin login pre-seeded, read-only-ish). Auto-resets daily via cron.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? One 5-minute YouTube video: "Migrate from Gumroad to your own VBWD store in 10 minutes." Screen recording, no face cam needed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Quickstart docs page: 4 commands from {\f1 git clone} to "first license key sold." Time-to-first-sale \u8804 ? 30 minutes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Migration script: read a Gumroad CSV export, create products + customers + (optionally regenerate) license keys in VBWD. {\b This is the conversion lever for Bucket B} \u8212- it removes the migration tax.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Set up a Discord server (or use GitHub Discussions). Single channel. Community moderates community. You read it once a day, max.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Output:} the platform sells itself in async; community catches first-line questions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 5\u8211-6 \u8212- Distribution: get listed where buyers already shop\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Goal: hand the hosting problem to platforms that already do it, while picking up free distribution.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Cloudron app store} submission. Cloudron has 50k+ self-hosters; they look there first. They run the customer's hosting; the customer buys the VBWD licence directly from you.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Coolify / Easypanel / CapRover templates} \u8212- submit a one-click deploy template for each. Same source repo, three packagings.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Elest.io app catalog} \u8212- reviewed catalog of self-hosted apps with {\b one-click managed deploy + ongoing managed hosting by Elest.io}. They take the customer's hosting fee; you get a small recurring rev-share. {\b This is the "managed hosting line" without you running ops.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Hetzner Cloud Marketplace snapshot} \u8212- pre-configured image, customer self-deploys in 2 minutes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Awesome-selfhosted} GitHub list \u8212- PR to add VBWD.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Output:} 5+ external surfaces where buyers find VBWD without you marketing. None of them require you to run hosting.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 7\u8211-8 \u8212- The Operator Cookbook (replaces "we host it for you")\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Goal: a paid product that teaches customers to self-host competently, eliminating the demand for you to do it yourself.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b "VBWD Operator Cookbook"} \u8212- paid \u8364 ?99 video + PDF: "How to self-host VBWD on a \u8364 ?15 Hetzner VPS, with backups, monitoring, SSL, updates, and recovery." 8\u8211-12 short videos (5 min each) + a checklist PDF + a sample {\f1 compose.yaml} and {\f1 .env}. Cover: provisioning, first-boot, Stripe wiring, daily backup script, restore drill, OS patching cadence, common failure modes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Sells from the same Stripe/landing page. Bundled into Pro and Enterprise tiers free; sold as a \u8364 ?99 add-on to Starter and Community users.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Why this exists:} when a non-technical buyer asks "do you offer hosting?" the answer is "no, but here's the \u8364 ?99 cookbook that walks you through doing it yourself in an afternoon \u8212- or pick Elest.io who'll do it managed for $50/mo." Both paths exist; you operate neither.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Set up {\b AlternativeTo.net} listing \u8212- claim the page, position as "Gumroad alternative."\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Set up {\b Stripe Apps marketplace} submission: small Stripe app that surfaces VBWD subscription metrics in the Stripe dashboard (~24h of work, recoups via Stripe-customer distribution).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Output:} the "do you host it for me?" question has two non-you answers \u8212- Elest.io for managed, Cookbook for DIY. You're never on the hook for ops.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 9\u8211-10 \u8212- Launch\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Goal: one big push that creates the lifetime-burst revenue and establishes the SEO inventory.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Product Hunt launch} \u8212- Tuesday morning EU time. Pre-line up 20 hunters via Twitter DMs (do this in week 8). Aim: top 5 of the day.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Show HN} the same week (Wednesday or Thursday). Title: "Show HN: Self-hosted Gumroad alternative \u8211- BSL 1.1, full source, $499/yr." Be ready to respond in comments for 4\u8211-6 hours; this is the one rule-violation-of-no-sync-work day.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b r/selfhosted, r/SaaS, r/IndieHackers} posts \u8212- different angle each, no copy-paste.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? Lifetime tier (\u8364 ?1,999, capped 30 sales) live for 7 days only. Counter on the page. Creates urgency.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? DM 30 newsletter writers in the indie/dev/SaaS space the day before launch. One-paragraph pitch. ~3\u8211-5 will mention you.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Output:} revenue spike from lifetime sales (target: 15+ sold = \u8364 ?30k brutto in one week), inbound from launch traffic (target: 1k+ landing visits, 30+ trial / community signups, 10+ paying conversions in 2 weeks).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 11\u8211-12 \u8212- Plugin marketplace MVP + SEO inventory\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Goal: open the plugin marketplace and seed the long-tail SEO that compounds for years.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Plugin marketplace MVP} \u8212- a {\f1 vbwd.io/plugins} page listing third-party plugins. MVP is a static page with Stripe Payment Links per plugin and a manifest format others can submit. Take 20% cut (0% for Enterprise publishers). No need for a full submission/review pipeline yet \u8212- start with manual approvals.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Affiliate program} \u8212- Rewardful or PartnerStack free tier. 20\u8211-30% recurring commission on referrals. Self-serve signup; no founder approval needed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Two cornerstone SEO articles} (no fluff):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i "Gumroad fees calculator: when does self-hosting break even?"} (with a real interactive calculator embedded \u8212- JS, no backend)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i "How to export everything from Gumroad before they change ToS again"} (high-intent rescue search)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Comparison pages} \u8212- one per competitor: {\f1 vbwd.io/vs/gumroad}, {\f1 /vs/lemon-squeezy}, {\f1 /vs/paddle}, {\f1 /vs/polar}. Honest, including where they win. These rank for "[X] alternative" queries forever.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u9744 ? {\b Reach out to one self-hosted-focused newsletter} (e.g., Self-Hosted podcast, Awesome-Selfhosted weekly) async \u8212- no call. Offer them a paid sponsorship or a guest article. \u8364 ?0\u8211-\u8364 ?500.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Output:} plugin marketplace live (revenue line opens), 6+ pages of high-intent SEO inventory live, affiliate program available for any visitor to sign up.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weeks 13+ (the ongoing rhythm after the 90 days)\par}
