{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 5. What you do NOT do (rules that protect the time budget)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These are non-negotiable for the part-time + no-contact constraint to hold.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b No sales calls. Ever.} Pricing page \u8594 ? Stripe \u8594 ? done. Anyone asking for a demo gets the demo URL + the YouTube video.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b No bespoke consulting} in Y1. The Owner Business Plan banks $27k from custom dev \u8212- it's poison for this plan because it requires meetings. If a customer offers \u8364 ?5k for a custom plugin, either (a) say no, or (b) quote \u8364 ?15k async-only with a 4-week SLA, and only do it on a burst weekend. Don't normalize it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b No founder-led support.} Email autoresponder: "Community support: Discord. Priority support: \u8364 ?299/yr add-on, async, 48h SLA." Buy the priority tier or wait in Discord.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab {\b No reseller / partner recruiting that requires meetings.} Affiliate program is fine (self-serve via Rewardful or similar). Active partner sales is Y2 work.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab {\b No new vertical decks until the launch nicheconverts.} The repo has decks for {\f1 agency}, {\f1 core}, {\f1 doctor}, {\f1 hotel}, {\f1 softwarestore} \u8212- pick one (recommend {\f1 softwarestore}), launch with that, ignore the others until that one prints \u8364 ?5k+/month.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab {\b No "we'll think about pricing later."} Pricing on the page from week 2. If you don't know the price, you don't have a product.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab {\b No commits to the customer roadmap.} Public roadmap on GitHub Discussions, customer votes, you ship what you want when you want. "Enterprise feature requests" route to "Enterprise tier \u8364 ?4,999/yr or fork it."\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab {\b No own-brand managed hosting.} No "VBWD Cloud" tier you operate. When customers ask "do you host this?" the only answers are: (a) Elest.io for managed (you collect rev-share, they handle ops), (b) the \u8364 ?99 Operator Cookbook for DIY, (c) "no, but here's our partner directory" once a white-label hosting partner exists in Y2. {\b Never} spin up a VPS for a customer yourself. Once you do it once, you've set a precedent.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 9.\tx360\tab {\b No uptime SLAs.} SLAs in this plan are on {\b email response time}, not on system uptime. You can't promise uptime for software the customer hosts. Anyone demanding an uptime SLA gets routed to Elest.io.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
